Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT , November 15
UNITED NATIONS -- The United Nations Security Council suspended its meeting on Iraq 's letter late Saturday night .
The Council was expected to take actions after reviewing the letter , but it failed to reach consensus .
Iraq sent a letter to U.N. chief Kofi Annan Saturday morning , saying that it had decided to rescind its decisions of August 5 and October 31 and resume full and complete cooperation with the United Nations arms inspectors .
( UN-Iraq-Suspension )
