BELGRADE -- U.S. envoy Christopher Hill said Saturday that the time has arrived to work out a new formula to carry forward the peace process in Kosovo , the Tanjug news agency reported .
" I think we are coming to the point where we start thinking about what this agreement is going to look like , get all the details down , " he said in Pristina , capital of Kosovo , after a meeting with Ibrahim Rugova , leader of Kosovo 's ethnic Albanian majority .
Describing the discussion as " very good , " Hill said they agreed in general on a timetable for a proposed new peace accord to solve the Kosovo crisis .
( Yugoslavia-Kosovo-US Envoy )
